<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName genus="I." lsidName="I. vallicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="vallicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">I. vallicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="I." lsidName="I. rigioclada" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="rigioclada">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">I. rigioclada</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Craib by sharing the procumbent habit, relatively small leaves and the similar flower shape, but it clearly differs from the latter by its usually 13-17-foliolate, flowers 3-5 mm long, calyx teeth triangular-lanceolate, and legumes 1-2 mm in diameter.
</paragraph>
