<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="9" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Flowering occurs from September to November, fruiting from October to December.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="9" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huan C. Wang &amp; Jin L. Liu" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Indigofera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Indigofera vallicola" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vallicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">Indigofera vallicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to southwest China, where it has only been collected from two localities (ca. 45 km apart from each other) in central Yunnan to date: Xiao Luzhi (type locality) in Luzhijiang valley and Ainishan village in Shuangbai County. The climate in its habitat is seasonally hot and arid. In the type locality, 
<taxonomicName genus="I." lsidName="I. vallicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="vallicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="9">I. vallicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
